    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Track mentions of keywords with HTTP / REST API and Discord on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** Social Listening · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nTrack mentions of keywords with HTTP / REST API and Discord on autopilot. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual listening is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Fetch Target Page → Extract Listings (CSS) → Rows from Arrays → Diff vs Last Run → Alert New Findings → Merge Diff Outcomes → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to social listening without manual effort\n- Anyone automating listening in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Discord webhook URL; Google OAuth2 / service account.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "d088d0ee-99f9-b3af-1f1e-405c65834ba3",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
